2021 Narrative:
Rehabilitation/equipping of 10 labs at 5 VET colleges (one college is in Eastern districts of Abkhazia) completed, modern equipment put in use at VET schools and VET educators trained  in the use of ICT and modern VET equipment for educational purposes;
>Teaching methodologies and management skills of about 60 VET teachers and managers updated through a series of international training on Life-Long-Learning (LLL) skills, digitalization of education process (both face-to-face and online) with focus on practical training in high-demand working professions, entrepreneurship, and teaching STEM subjects;
>About 300 VET colleges students and school children were effectively engaged in career orientation at the Career Guidance Centers through a series of seminars, workshops, professional trainings and master classes by private entrepreneurs;
>Cooperation schemes and dialogue established with private and public employers by involving private companies and successful individuals into developing apprenticeship VET programs and the elements of dual education;
>Vocational education further popularized in Abkhazia through producing social media content, commissioning multimedia documentaries on working professions and a series of media interviews. About 30 news reports and interviews related to VET working professions prepared and delivered over TV broadcasting and over social media.

FAO: Trained 14 Plant Protection Specialists (teachers of agronomy and extensionists) of Abkhazia on the best practices in pest management through a 24-month curriculum.

